{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897271756,"sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb9dd94001Ra1VqIHL1Tky3U","messageID":"msg_d7bb9c9c8001E0lm91E350Yuhh","sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c3716bfde3664fbba5d2105e416a36ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Task Checklist\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This task checklist breaks down the implementation of E2E integration tests for the AgentCube project into atomic, independently verifiable tasks.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `test/e2e`  \n8: **Language:** Go  \n9: **Size:** L  \n10: **Status:** Ready for Implementation\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Phase 1: Foundation (Framework Infrastructure)\n15: \n16: ### 1.1 Create Test Framework Structure\n17: \n18: **Task ID:** T-1.1  \n19: **Description:** Create directory structure and package initialization for E2E test framework\n20: \n21: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n22: - Directory `test/e2e/framework/` exists\n23: - Directory `test/e2e/agentruntime/` exists\n24: - Directory `test/e2e/codeinterpreter/` exists\n25: - Directory `test/e2e/integration/` exists\n26: - Directory `test/e2e/manifests/` exists\n27: - Directory `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/` exists\n28: - Directory `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/` exists\n29: - Directory `test/e2e/manifests/deployments/` exists\n30: - All directories contain `go.mod` package declaration `package e2e` or `package framework`\n31: - `go build ./test/e2e/...` succeeds without errors\n32: \n33: **Dependencies:** None  \n34: **Estimated Time:** 30 minutes\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### 1.2 Implement TestFramework Core\n39: \n40: **Task ID:** T-1.2  \n41: **Description:** Implement core TestFramework struct with Kubernetes client initialization\n42: \n43: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/framework.go`\n44: \n45: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n46: - `TestFramework` struct exists with fields: config, clientset, agentClient, namespace, clusterName, httpClient, cleanup\n47: - `FrameworkOptions` struct exists with configurable options\n48: - `NewDefaultFramework(name string) *TestFramework` function works and returns framework with defaults\n49: - `NewFramework(name string, opts FrameworkOptions) *TestFramework` function works and accepts custom options\n50: - Default namespace format is `e2e-test-<random>` when not specified\n51: - Default timeout is 5 minutes when not specified\n52: - Default poll interval is 1 second when not specified\n53: - `go test -c ./test/e2e/framework/` compiles successfully\n54: - Unit tests verify framework initialization with various options\n55: \n56: **Dependencies:** T-1.1  \n57: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### 1.3 Implement Kubernetes Environment Setup\n62: \n63: **Task ID:** T-1.3  \n64: **Description:** Add Kubernetes environment setup and teardown methods to TestFramework\n65: \n66: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/framework.go` (extend)\n67: \n68: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n69: - `AgentCubeReady() bool` method checks if AgentCube deployment is ready\n70: - `Setup() error` method creates test namespace if needed\n71: - `Cleanup() error` method deletes test namespace and registered cleanup functions\n72: - `Namespace() string` method returns current test namespace\n73: - `Clientset() *kubernetes.Clientset` method returns Kubernetes client\n74: - `AgentClient() *agentclient.Clientset` method returns AgentCube client\n75: - Cleanup functions are executed in reverse order\n76: - Setup creates namespace with random suffix if not specified\n77: - Cleanup respects `SkipCleanup` option\n78: - Unit tests verify setup/teardown behavior\n79: \n80: **Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n81: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ### 1.4 Implement AgentRuntimeHelper\n86: \n87: **Task ID:** T-1.4  \n88: **Description:** Implement helper utilities for AgentRuntime CRUD operations\n89: \n90: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go`\n91: \n92: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n93: - `AgentRuntimeHelper` struct exists with framework reference\n94: - `NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f *TestFramework) *AgentRuntimeHelper` constructor works\n95: - `CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, agent) (*AgentRuntime, error)` creates AgentRuntime resource\n96: - `GetAgentRuntime(ctx, name) (*AgentRuntime, error)` retrieves AgentRuntime by name\n97: - `WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, name, timeout) error` waits until AgentRuntime is ready\n98: - `CreateSession(ctx, req) (*CreateSandboxResponse, error)` creates session via workload-manager\n99: - `InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, headers) (*InvokeResponse, error)` invokes session\n100: - `DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID) error` deletes session\n101: - All methods handle context cancellation properly\n102: - Unit tests verify each helper method\n103: \n104: **Dependencies:** T-1.3  \n105: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### 1.5 Implement CodeInterpreterHelper\n110: \n111: **Task ID:** T-1.5  \n112: **Description:** Implement helper utilities for CodeInterpreter operations\n113: \n114: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go` (extend)\n115: \n116: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n117: - `CodeInterpreterHelper` struct exists with framework reference\n118: - `NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f *TestFramework) *CodeInterpreterHelper` constructor works\n119: - `CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci) (*CodeInterpreter, error)` creates CodeInterpreter resource\n120: - `GetCodeInterpreter(ctx, name) (*CodeInterpreter, error)` retrieves CodeInterpreter by name\n121: - `WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, name, timeout) error` waits until CodeInterpreter is ready\n122: - `ExecuteCode(ctx, sessionID, code) (*ExecuteResponse, error)` executes code in session\n123: - `UploadFile(ctx, sessionID, filename, content) error` uploads file to session\n124: - `DownloadFile(ctx, sessionID, filename) ([]byte, error)` downloads file from session\n125: - All methods handle context cancellation properly\n126: - Unit tests verify each helper method\n127: \n128: **Dependencies:** T-1.3  \n129: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ### 1.6 Implement Custom Assertions\n134: \n135: **Task ID:** T-1.6  \n136: **Description:** Implement custom Gomega matchers for common assertions\n137: \n138: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/assertions.go`\n139: \n140: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n141: - `EventuallyWithTimeout(actual, timeout, intervals) AsyncAssertion` wrapper exists\n142: - `ConsistentlyWithTimeout(actual, timeout, intervals) AsyncAssertion` wrapper exists\n143: - `HaveConditions(expected...) OmegaMatcher` verifies resource conditions\n144: - `BeReady() OmegaMatcher` verifies resource Ready status is true\n145: - `HavePhase(phase) OmegaMatcher` verifies resource phase matches\n146: - `HaveEndpoint(endpoint) OmegaMatcher` verifies service endpoint exists\n147: - `ReturnSuccess() OmegaMatcher` verifies HTTP 2xx response\n148: - `ReturnStatusCode(code) OmegaMatcher` verifies specific HTTP status code\n149: - `HaveSessionID() OmegaMatcher` verifies response contains session ID\n150: - All matchers have descriptive failure messages\n151: - Unit tests verify each matcher behavior\n152: \n153: **Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n154: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### 1.7 Create Test Fixtures\n159: \n160: **Task ID:** T-1.7  \n161: **Description:** Implement fixture generators for test resources\n162: \n163: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/fixtures.go`\n164: \n165: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n166: - `NewTestAgentRuntime(name) *AgentRuntime` creates AgentRuntime with minimal valid spec\n167: - `NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec(name, spec) *AgentRuntime` creates AgentRuntime with custom spec\n168: - `NewTestCodeInterpreter(name) *CodeInterpreter` creates CodeInterpreter with minimal valid spec\n169: - `NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec(name, spec) *CodeInterpreter` creates CodeInterpreter with custom spec\n170: - `NewTestSessionRequest(kind, name, namespace) *CreateSandboxRequest` creates session request\n171: - `NewTestInvokePayload(data map[string]interface{}) []byte` creates JSON payload\n172: - Fixtures use sensible defaults (e.g., nginx:latest for container image)\n173: - Fixtures include required fields for resource creation\n174: - Unit tests verify fixture generation\n175: \n176: **Dependencies:** T-1.4, T-1.5  \n177: **Estimated Time:** 1.5 hours\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests\n182: \n183: ### 2.1 Implement AgentRuntime Test Suite\n184: \n185: **Task ID:** T-2.1  \n186: **Description:** Create main AgentRuntime E2E test suite with Ginkgo\n187: \n188: **File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/agentruntime_suite_test.go`\n189: \n190: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n191: - Test suite file exists with proper package declaration\n192: - `Describe(\"AgentRuntime E2E\", func() { ... })` top-level describe block\n193: - `BeforeSuite` initializes framework and waits for AgentCube to be ready\n194: - `AfterSuite` performs cleanup unless `SkipCleanup` is enabled\n195: - Framework and helper variables declared at suite level\n196: - Namespace variable declared at suite level\n197: - `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/` runs without errors\n198: - `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/ -ginkgo.v` shows suite structure\n199: \n200: **Dependencies:** T-1.7  \n201: **Estimated Time:** 1 hour\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ### 2.2 Implement AgentRuntime Creation Tests\n206: \n207: **Task ID:** T-2.2  \n208: **Description:** Implement tests for AgentRuntime creation workflows\n209: \n210: **File:** `test/e2e/agentruntime/creation_test.go`\n211: \n212: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n213: - `Context(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() { ... })` context block\n214: 