ents exponential backoff with jitter\n583: - Retryable returns last error on failure\n584: - `EventuallyRetryable(actual, timeout, pollingInterval, maxRetries)` wrapper exists\n585: - Retryable respects context cancellation\n586: - Unit tests verify retry behavior\n587: - Unit tests verify backoff calculation\n588: - Integration test uses Retryable for known flaky operation\n589: - `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Retry` passes\n590: \n591: **Dependencies:** T-1.6  \n592: **Estimated Time:** 1.5 hours\n593: \n594: ---\n595: \n596: ### 5.3 Implement Timeout Management Utilities\n597: \n598: **Task ID:** T-5.3  \n599: **Description:** Implement timeout context utilities for test operations\n600: \n601: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/timeout.go`\n602: \n603: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n604: - `TimeoutContext(timeout) (ctx, cancel)` function exists\n605: - `WithDefaultTimeout() (ctx, cancel)` function exists (5 minute default)\n606: - Timeout contexts log when timeout occurs\n607: - Cancel functions clean up resources properly\n608: - Timeout contexts handle nested timeouts correctly\n609: - Unit tests verify timeout behavior\n610: - Unit tests verify cancellation behavior\n611: - Integration test demonstrates timeout handling\n612: - `go test ./test/e2e/framework/ -run Timeout` passes\n613: \n614: **Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n615: **Estimated Time:** 1 hour\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ### 5.4 Implement Test Reporting\n620: \n621: **Task ID:** T-5.4  \n622: **Description:** Implement custom test reporting with multiple output formats\n623: \n624: **File:** `test/e2e/framework/reporting.go`\n625: \n626: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n627: - `TestReporter` struct exists with outputPath field\n628: - `Report(report)` method exists\n629: - `generateHTMLReport(reportData)` generates HTML report\n630: - `generateJSONReport(reportData)` generates JSON report\n631: - `generateJUnitReport(reportData)` generates JUnit XML report\n632: - Reports include: summary, specs, duration, pass/fail counts\n633: - Reports are saved to `test/e2e/reports/` directory\n634: - HTML report is human-readable with filtering\n635: - JSON report is machine-readable\n636: - JUnit report is CI/CD compatible\n637: - Reporter is registered with Ginkgo\n638: - `go test ./test/e2e/... -ginkgo.report` generates all reports\n639: \n640: **Dependencies:** T-1.2  \n641: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n642: \n643: ---\n644: \n645: ### 5.5 Create Test Manifests\n646: \n647: **Task ID:** T-5.5  \n648: **Description:** Create test manifest YAML files for test resources\n649: \n650: **Files:**\n651: - `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml`\n652: - `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/multi-container-agent.yaml`\n653: - `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml`\n654: - `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/node-interpreter.yaml`\n655: - `test/e2e/manifests/deployments/agentcube-minimal.yaml`\n656: \n657: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n658: - All manifests use template syntax for namespace `{{ .Namespace }}`\n659: - All manifests are valid Kubernetes YAML\n660: - All manifests are valid AgentCube CRDs\n661: - `simple-agent.yaml` creates minimal AgentRuntime with nginx\n662: - `multi-container-agent.yaml` creates AgentRuntime with 2 containers\n663: - `python-interpreter.yaml` creates CodeInterpreter with Python 3.11\n664: - `node-interpreter.yaml` creates CodeInterpreter with Node.js\n665: - `agentcube-minimal.yaml` is minimal AgentCube deployment\n666: - `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml` works (with namespace substitution)\n667: - `kubectl apply -f test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml` works (with namespace substitution)\n668: \n669: **Dependencies:** T-1.7  \n670: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n671: \n672: ---\n673: \n674: ## Phase 6: Documentation\n675: \n676: ### 6.1 Write E2E Test Documentation\n677: \n678: **Task ID:** T-6.1  \n679: **Description:** Create comprehensive documentation for E2E test suite\n680: \n681: **File:** `test/e2e/README.md`\n682: \n683: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n684: - README exists with:\n685:   - Overview of E2E test suite\n686:   - Prerequisites (Go, kind/k3s, kubectl, Docker)\n687:   - Installation instructions\n688:   - Architecture diagram (from design.md)\n689:   - Running tests locally (kind setup, load images, deploy, run tests)\n690:   - Running tests in CI/CD (GitHub Actions workflow reference)\n691:   - Test organization (directory structure, test categories)\n692:   - Writing new tests (patterns, helpers, assertions)\n693:   - Debugging failed tests (diagnostics, logs)\n694:   - Performance testing (load tests, stress tests)\n695: - All code blocks are copy-pasteable and work\n696: - All file paths are correct\n697: - All commands are tested and verified\n698: - `test -f test/e2e/README.md` succeeds\n699: \n700: **Dependencies:** T-5.5  \n701: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n702: \n703: ---\n704: \n705: ### 6.2 Create Running Tests Guide\n706: \n707: **Task ID:** T-6.2  \n708: **Description:** Create detailed step-by-step guide for running E2E tests\n709: \n710: **File:** `test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md`\n711: \n712: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n713: - RUNNING_TESTS.md exists with:\n714:   - Local development setup (kind cluster creation, image loading, deployment)\n715:   - Quick start (single command to run all tests)\n716:   - Running specific test suites (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Integration)\n717:   - Running specific tests (Ginkgo focus filter)\n718:   - Running tests with options (verbose, parallel, skip cleanup)\n719:   - Running tests with race detector\n720:   - Running tests with coverage\n721:   - Troubleshooting common issues (cluster not ready, image not found, timeout)\n722:   - Interpreting test results (reading reports, understanding failures)\n723: - All commands are copy-pasteable and work\n724: - All file paths are correct\n725: - All commands are tested and verified\n726: - `test -f test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md` succeeds\n727: \n728: **Dependencies:** T-6.1  \n729: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n730: \n731: ---\n732: \n733: ### 6.3 Document Test Patterns\n734: \n735: **Task ID:** T-6.3  \n736: **Description:** Document common test patterns and best practices\n737: \n738: **File:** `test/e2e/PATTERNS.md`\n739: \n740: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n741: - PATTERNS.md exists with:\n742:   - Test structure patterns (Describe/Context/It hierarchy)\n743:   - Setup/teardown patterns (BeforeSuite/AfterSuite, BeforeEach/AfterEach)\n744:   - Assertion patterns (custom assertions, matchers)\n745:   - Helper usage patterns (agent runtime helper, code interpreter helper)\n746:   - Fixture usage patterns (resource fixtures, payload fixtures)\n747:   - Error handling patterns (error verification, timeout handling)\n748:   - Concurrency patterns (goroutines, WaitGroup, channels)\n749:   - Isolation patterns (per-test namespaces, resource cleanup)\n750:   - Retry patterns (Retryable, EventuallyRetryable)\n751:   - Each pattern includes:\n752:     - Description\n753:     - When to use\n754:     - Example code\n755:     - Common pitfalls\n756: - All code examples are valid and tested\n757: - All file paths are correct\n758: - `test -f test/e2e/PATTERNS.md` succeeds\n759: \n760: **Dependencies:** T-6.2  \n761: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n762: \n763: ---\n764: \n765: ### 6.4 Document CI/CD Integration\n766: \n767: **Task ID:** T-6.4  \n768: **Description:** Create CI/CD workflow for running E2E tests\n769: \n770: **File:** `.github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml`\n771: \n772: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n773: - GitHub Actions workflow exists with:\n774:   - Trigger conditions (push to main/develop, pull request)\n775:   - Job setup (checkout, Go setup, kind setup)\n776:   - Build step (docker build, kind load)\n777:   - Deploy step (apply CRDs, apply deployment, wait for ready)\n778:   - Test step (run E2E tests with timeout)\n779:   - Upload artifacts step (upload test results, reports, diagnostics)\n780:   - Cleanup step (delete cluster)\n781: - Workflow runs successfully on GitHub Actions\n782: - Workflow uploads artifacts on both success and failure\n783: - Workflow runs all E2E tests\n784: - Workflow completes within 45 minutes\n785: - `test -f .github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml` succeeds\n786: \n787: **Dependencies:** T-6.3  \n788: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n789: \n790: ---\n791: \n792: ## Phase 7: Performance & Security\n793: \n794: ### 7.1 Implement Load Testing\n795: \n796: **Task ID:** T-7.1  \n797: **Description:** Implement load testing utilities and tests\n798: \n799: **File:** `test/e2e/integration/load_test.go`\n800: \n801: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n802: - `LoadTest(ctx, helper, agentName, concurrency, duration) error` function exists\n803: - LoadTest creates concurrent sessions for specified duration\n804: - LoadTest collects errors and metrics\n805: - LoadTest measures throughput (requests/second)\n806: - LoadTest measures latency (p50, p95, p99)\n807: - LoadTest measures error rate\n808: - `It(\"should handle 100 concurrent invocations for 5 minutes\")` test exists\n809: - Test verifies error rate < 1%\n810: - Test verifies p95 latency < 1s\n811: - Test logs performance metrics\n812: - Test has appropriate timeout (10 minutes)\n813: - `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Load` passes with valid deployment\n814: \n815: **Dependencies:** T-4.4  \n816: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n817: \n818: ---\n819: \n820: ### 7.2 Implement Stress Testing\n821: \n822: **Task ID:** T-7.2  \n823: **Description:** Implement stress testing utilities and tests\n824: \n825: **File:** `test/e2e/integration/stress_test.go`\n826: \n827: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n828: - `StressTest(ctx, helper, count) error` function exists\n829: - StressTest creates many resources concurrently\n830: - StressTest creates many sessions concurrently\n831: - StressTest measures resource creation time\n832: - StressTest measures memory usage\n833: - StressTest measures CPU usage\n834: - `It(\"should handle 100 concurrent AgentRuntime creations\")` test exists\n835: - `It(\"should handle 1000 concurrent session creations\")` test exists\n836: - Tests verify system doesn't crash under stress\n837: - Tests verify graceful degradation\n838: - Tests log resource metrics\n839: - Tests have appropriate timeouts (15 minutes)\n840: - `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Stress` passes with valid deployment\n841: \n842: **Dependencies:** T-7.1  \n843: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n844: \n845: ---\n846: \n847: ### 7.3 Implement Security Testing\n848: \n849: **Task ID:** T-7.3  \n850: **Description:** Implement security-focused E2E tests\n851: \n852: **File:** `test/e2e/integration/security_test.go`\n853: \n854: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n855: - `Describe(\"Security\", func() { ... })` describe block\n856: - `BeforeSuite` initializes framework and waits for AgentCube to be ready\n857: - `It(\"should reject unauthorized session creation\")` verifies auth enforcement\n858: - `It(\"should reject unauthorized session invocation\")` verifies auth enforcement\n859: - `It(\"should isolate sessions by namespace\")` verifies namespace isolation\n860: - `It(\"should not leak data between sessions\")` verifies session isolation\n861: - `It(\"should handle malicious payloads\")` verifies input validation\n862: - `It(\"should enforce resource quotas\")` verifies quota enforcement\n863: - Tests verify authentication failures\n864: - Tests verify authorization failures\n865: - Tests verify isolation boundaries\n866: - Tests verify input sanitization\n867: - Tests verify quota limits\n868: - Tests have appropriate timeouts\n869: - `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Security` passes with valid deployment\n870: \n871: **Dependencies:** T-7.2  \n872: **Estimated Time:** 3 hours\n873: \n874: ---\n875: \n876: ### 7.4 Create Performance Baselines\n877: \n878: **Task ID:** T-7.4  \n879: **Description:** Establish and document performance baselines\n880: \n881: **File:** `test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md`\n882: \n883: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n884: - BENCHMARKS.md exists with:\n885:   - Session creation latency baseline (target: < 2s p95)\n886:   - Session invocation latency baseline (target: < 100ms p95)\n887:   - Concurrent session throughput baseline (target: > 100 sessions/sec)\n888:   - AgentRuntime creation time baseline (target: < 30s)\n889:   - CodeInterpreter execution time baseline (target: < 500ms for simple code)\n890:   - Resource usage baselines (CPU, memory, network)\n891:   - Load testing thresholds (concurrency, duration, error rate)\n892:   - Stress testing thresholds (resource count, session count)\n893:   - How to run benchmarks\n894:   - How to compare against baselines\n895: - All baselines are measured and documented\n896: - All baselines include measurement methodology\n897: - All baselines include acceptable ranges\n898: - `test -f test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md` succeeds\n899: - `go test ./test/e2e/integration/ -run Benchmarks` generates baseline metrics\n900: \n901: **Dependencies:** T-7.3  \n902: **Estimated Time:** 2 hours\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## Verification Criteria\n907: \n908: ### Completion Checklist\n909: \n910: - [ ] All Phase 1 tasks (T-1.1 through T-1.7) are completed\n911: - [ ] All Phase 2 tasks (T-2.1 through T-2.6) are completed\n912: - [ ] All Phase 3 tasks (T-3.1 through T-3.5) are completed\n913: - [ ] All Phase 4 tasks (T-4.1 through T-4.4) are completed\n914: - [ ] All Phase 5 tasks (T-5.1 through T-5.5) are completed\n915: - [ ] All Phase 6 tasks (T-6.1 through T-6.4) are completed\n916: - [ ] All Phase 7 tasks (T-7.1 through T-7.4) are completed\n917: \n918: ### Integration Testing\n919: \n920: - [ ] `go build ./test/e2e/...` succeeds without errors\n921: - [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/framework/...` passes all unit tests\n922: - [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/agentruntime/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n923: - [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/codeinterpreter/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n924: - [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/integration/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n925: - [ ] `go test ./test/e2e/...` passes all tests with valid deployment\n926: - [ ] `go test -race ./test/e2e/...` passes all tests without race conditions\n927: - [ ] `go test -cover ./test/e2e/...` achieves > 80% code coverage\n928: \n929: ### Documentation Verification\n930: \n931: - [ ] `test/e2e/README.md` exists and is complete\n932: - [ ] `test/e2e/RUNNING_TESTS.md` exists and is complete\n933: - [ ] `test/e2e/PATTERNS.md` exists and is complete\n934: - [ ] `test/e2e/BENCHMARKS.md` exists and is complete\n935: - [ ] `.github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml` exists and runs successfully on GitHub Actions\n936: \n937: ### Smoke Tests\n938: \n939: - [ ] E2E test suite runs successfully in kind cluster\n940: - [ ] E2E test suite generates test reports\n941: - [ ] E2E test suite collects diagnostics on failures\n942: - [ ] E2E test suite completes within 30 minutes\n943: - [ ] E2E test suite achieves acceptable performance (meets baselines)\n944: \n945: ---\n946: \n947: ## Total Estimated Time\n948: \n949: - Phase 1: Foundation - 13 hours\n950: - Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests - 13.5 hours\n951: - Phase 3: CodeInterpreter Tests - 12 hours\n952: - Phase 4: Integration Tests - 12.5 hours\n953: - Phase 5: Test Infrastructure - 10.5 hours\n954: - Phase 6: Documentation - 9 hours\n955: - Phase 7: Performance & Security - 11 hours\n956: \n957: **Total: 81.5 hours**\n958: \n959: ---\n960: \n961: ## Notes\n962: \n963: 1. All tasks should be completed sequentially within each phase\n964: 2. Tasks in different phases can be completed in parallel if dependencies are met\n965: 3. Each task must pass its acceptance criteria before marking as complete\n966: 4. Integration tests require a valid AgentCube deployment in a Kubernetes cluster\n967: 5. Performance tests (Phase 7) should be run on dedicated hardware for accurate results\n968: 6. Security tests (T-7.3) require understanding of AgentCube security model\n969: 7. CI/CD integration (T-6.4) should be tested on a real GitHub repository\n\n(End of file - total 969 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Task Checklist\n\n## Overview\n\nThis task checklist breaks down the implementation of E2E integration tests for the AgentCube project into atomic, independently verifiable tasks.\n\n**Module:** `test/e2e`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n**Status:** Ready for Implementation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Framework Infrastructure)\n\n### 1.1 Create Test Framework Structure\n\n**Task ID:** T-1.1  \n**Description:** Create directory structure and package initialization for E2E test framework\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775897271732,"end":1775897271753}}}}
