{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775897276515,"sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb9f060001HfT6h6P7jVCbjd","messageID":"msg_d7bb9de02001vvcxp5proEwHZU","sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897279312,"sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb9f6b8001A3QrTm1DR4AR9f","messageID":"msg_d7bb9de02001vvcxp5proEwHZU","sessionID":"ses_28446533dffeWNSknzWye520EF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fb164017523943139cacb99c37d03b9e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041 Delta Specification: E2E 集成测试\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Provide end-to-end integration tests for the agentcube project, covering the complete lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the client-go library, including CRUD operations, watch/informer/lister functionality, error handling, and fake client behavior.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### REQ-001: AgentRuntime Lifecycle Integration Tests\n9: \n10: **Description**: Verify that AgentRuntime resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n11: \n12: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n13: - AgentRuntime creation succeeds with valid spec\n14: - AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name and namespace\n15: - AgentRuntime spec updates are persisted\n16: - AgentRuntime status updates are persisted independently of spec\n17: - AgentRuntime deletion removes the resource\n18: - AgentRuntime list operations return correct resources\n19: - Watch operations receive events for AgentRuntime changes\n20: \n21: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n22: \n23: ```\n24: Scenario: Create AgentRuntime with valid spec\n25:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n26:     AND a valid AgentRuntime spec with required fields (agent type, image, resource limits)\n27:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is created in a test namespace\n28:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n29:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has a generated UID\n30:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has creation timestamp set\n31:     AND the AgentRuntime spec matches the input spec\n32:     AND the AgentRuntime status is initialized to empty\n33: \n34: Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime by name\n35:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource in a test namespace\n36:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is retrieved by its name\n37:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n38:     AND the returned AgentRuntime matches the stored resource\n39:     AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n40: \n41: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime spec\n42:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n43:     AND a modified AgentRuntime spec (e.g., updated image tag)\n44:   WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n45:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n46:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated spec\n47:     AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n48:     AND the AgentRuntime status is preserved unchanged\n49: \n50: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status independently\n51:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n52:     AND an updated status (e.g., phase = Running, agentID set)\n53:   WHEN the AgentRuntime status is updated using UpdateStatus\n54:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n55:     AND the returned AgentRuntime has the updated status\n56:     AND the AgentRuntime resourceVersion is incremented\n57:     AND the AgentRuntime spec is preserved unchanged\n58: \n59: Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n60:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n61:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted by name\n62:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n63:     AND subsequent retrieval of the AgentRuntime returns \"not found\" error\n64:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from list results\n65: \n66: Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n67:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n68:     AND AgentRuntime resources in other namespaces\n69:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed in the specific namespace\n70:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n71:     AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes from that namespace\n72:     AND all AgentRuntimes in the namespace are present\n73:     AND AgentRuntimes from other namespaces are not present\n74: \n75: Scenario: List AgentRuntimes cluster-wide\n76:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources across different namespaces\n77:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with no namespace filter\n78:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n79:     AND the list contains AgentRuntimes from all namespaces\n80:     AND all AgentRuntimes in the cluster are present\n81: \n82: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for create events\n83:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n84:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in a test namespace\n85:   WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created in the namespace\n86:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n87:     AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n88:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n89: \n90: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for update events\n91:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n92:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n93:   WHEN the AgentRuntime spec is updated\n94:   THEN the watch channel receives a MODIFIED event\n95:     AND the event contains the updated AgentRuntime\n96:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Modified)\n97: \n98: Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime for delete events\n99:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n100:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes in its namespace\n101:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted\n102:   THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n103:     AND the event contains the AgentRuntime before deletion\n104:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-002: CodeInterpreter Lifecycle Integration Tests\n110: \n111: **Description**: Verify that CodeInterpreter resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n112: \n113: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n114: - CodeInterpreter creation succeeds with valid spec\n115: - CodeInterpreter can be retrieved by name and namespace\n116: - CodeInterpreter spec updates are persisted\n117: - CodeInterpreter status updates are persisted independently of spec\n118: - CodeInterpreter deletion removes the resource\n119: - CodeInterpreter list operations return correct resources\n120: - Watch operations receive events for CodeInterpreter changes\n121: \n122: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n123: \n124: ```\n125: Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter with valid spec\n126:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset for agentcube runtime API\n127:     AND a valid CodeInterpreter spec with required fields (code, runtime, language)\n128:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is created in a test namespace\n129:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n130:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has a generated UID\n131:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has creation timestamp set\n132:     AND the CodeInterpreter spec matches the input spec\n133:     AND the CodeInterpreter status is initialized to empty\n134: \n135: Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter by name\n136:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n137:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by its name\n138:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n139:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n140:     AND all fields including metadata, spec, and status are preserved\n141: \n142: Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter spec\n143:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n144:     AND a modified CodeInterpreter spec (e.g., updated code content)\n145:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter spec is updated\n146:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n147:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated spec\n148:     AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n149:     AND the CodeInterpreter status is preserved unchanged\n150: \n151: Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter status independently\n152:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n153:     AND an updated status (e.g., executionResult, output)\n154:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter status is updated using UpdateStatus\n155:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n156:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter has the updated status\n157:     AND the CodeInterpreter resourceVersion is incremented\n158:     AND the CodeInterpreter spec is preserved unchanged\n159: \n160: Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n161:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n162:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted by name\n163:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n164:     AND subsequent retrieval of the CodeInterpreter returns \"not found\" error\n165:     AND the CodeInterpreter is removed from list results\n166: \n167: Scenario: List CodeInterpreters in namespace\n168:   GIVEN multiple CodeInterpreter resources in a test namespace\n169:     AND CodeInterpreter resources in other namespaces\n170:   WHEN CodeInterpreters are listed in the specific namespace\n171:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n172:     AND the list contains only CodeInterpreters from that namespace\n173:     AND all CodeInterpreters in the namespace are present\n174:     AND CodeInterpreters from other namespaces are not present\n175: \n176: Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for create events\n177:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n178:     AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in a test namespace\n179:   WHEN a new CodeInterpreter is created in the namespace\n180:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n181:     AND the event contains the newly created CodeInterpreter\n182:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Added)\n183: \n184: Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter for delete events\n185:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource\n186:     AND an active watch channel for CodeInterpreters in its namespace\n187:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is deleted\n188:   THEN the watch channel receives a DELETED event\n189:     AND the event contains the CodeInterpreter before deletion\n190:     AND the event type is correct (v1.Deleted)\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### REQ-003: Informer and Lister Integration Tests\n196: \n197: **Description**: Verify that SharedInformerFactory and listers work correctly for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including cache synchronization and event handling.\n198: \n199: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n200: - Informers successfully start and sync cache\n201: - Listers return cached resources\n202: - Informer event handlers receive resource changes\n203: - Multiple informers can share the same factory\n204: - Cache resync works correctly\n205: \n206: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n207: \n208: ```\n209: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer syncs existing resources\n210:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in a test namespace\n211:     AND a SharedInformerFactory configured for the namespace\n212:     AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n213:   WHEN the informer is started\n214:     AND WaitForCacheSync is called\n215:   THEN the cache sync completes successfully\n216:     AND the AgentRuntime lister returns all existing AgentRuntimes\n217:     AND all resources are cached with correct metadata\n218: \n219: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives create events\n220:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer\n221:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n222:   WHEN a new AgentRuntime is created\n223:   THEN the event handler receives an OnAdd event\n224:     AND the event handler is called with the new AgentRuntime\n225:     AND the AgentRuntime is immediately available in the lister cache\n226: \n227: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives update events\n228:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n229:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n230:   WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is updated\n231:   THEN the event handler receives an OnUpdate event\n232:     AND the event handler is called with old and new objects\n233:     AND the updated AgentRuntime is immediately reflected in the lister cache\n234: \n235: Scenario: AgentRuntime informer receives delete events\n236:   GIVEN a started AgentRuntime informer with existing resources\n237:     AND a registered event handler for AgentRuntimes\n238:   WHEN an existing AgentRuntime is deleted\n239:   THEN the event handler receives an OnDelete event\n240:     AND the event handler is called with the deleted AgentRuntime\n241:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from the lister cache\n242: \n243: Scenario: Multiple informers share same factory\n244:   GIVEN a SharedInformerFactory configured for a test namespace\n245:     AND an AgentRuntime informer from the factory\n246:     AND a CodeInterpreter informer from the same factory\n247:   WHEN both informers are started\n248:     AND WaitForCacheSync is called for both types\n249:   THEN both informers sync successfully\n250:     AND both listers return correct resources\n251:     AND the factory manages a single cache for both resource types\n252: \n253: Scenario: AgentRuntime lister with label selector\n254:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources with different labels in a test namespace\n255:     AND a synced AgentRuntime lister\n256:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a label selector\n257:   THEN the list returns only AgentRuntimes matching the labels\n258:     AND non-matching AgentRuntimes are excluded\n259: \n260: Scenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister Get by name\n261:   GIVEN an existing CodeInterpreter resource in a test namespace\n262:     AND a synced CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n263:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter is retrieved by name using the namespace lister\n264:   THEN the retrieval succeeds with no error\n265:     AND the returned CodeInterpreter matches the stored resource\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ### REQ-004: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n271: \n272: **Description**: Verify that the client-go library handles errors, edge cases, and invalid inputs correctly.\n273: \n274: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n275: - Invalid spec returns appropriate error\n276: - Resource conflicts are detected\n277: - Watch handles disconnection and reconnection\n278: - Concurrent modifications are detected\n279: \n280: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n281: \n282: ```\n283: Scenario: Create AgentRuntime with invalid spec\n284:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n285:     AND an invalid AgentRuntime spec (missing required fields)\n286:   WHEN the AgentRuntime creation is attempted\n287:   THEN the creation fails with a validation error\n288:     AND the error message indicates the validation failure\n289:     AND no AgentRuntime resource is created\n290: \n291: Scenario: Update AgentRuntime with stale resourceVersion\n292:   GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime resource\n293:     AND an AgentRuntime object with an outdated resourceVersion\n294:   WHEN the AgentRuntime update is attempted\n295:   THEN the update fails with a conflict error\n296:     AND the error indicates resource version conflict\n297:     AND the AgentRuntime remains unchanged\n298: \n299: Scenario: Delete non-existent AgentRuntime\n300:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n301:     AND a non-existent AgentRuntime name in a test namespace\n302:   WHEN the AgentRuntime deletion is attempted\n303:   THEN the deletion fails with a \"not found\" error\n304: \n305: Scenario: Get non-existent CodeInterpreter\n306:   GIVEN a configured Kubernetes clientset\n307:     AND a non-existent CodeInterpreter name in a test namespace\n308:   WHEN the CodeInterpreter retrieval is attempted\n309:   THEN the retrieval fails with a \"not found\" error\n310: \n311: Scenario: Watch handles server disconnection\n312:   GIVEN an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n313:   WHEN the API server connection is temporarily lost\n314:     AND then re-established\n315:   THEN the watch channel reconnects automatically\n316:     AND events continue to be received after reconnection\n317:     AND no duplicate events are received for the same change\n318: \n319: Scenario: List with field selector\n320:   GIVEN multiple AgentRuntime resources in different states\n321:     AND a configured Kubernetes clientset\n322:   WHEN AgentRuntimes are listed with a field selector (e.g., status.phase=Running)\n323:   THEN the list succeeds with no error\n324:     AND the list contains only AgentRuntimes matching the field selector\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ### REQ-005: Fake Client Integration Tests\n330: \n331: **Description**: Verify that fake clients work correctly for testing purposes, including CRUD operations and watch behavior.\n332: \n333: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n334: - Fake clientset supports all CRUD operations\n335: - Fake clients track resources in memory\n336: - Watch operations work with fake clients\n337: - Fake clients can be used in unit tests\n338: \n339: **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios**:\n340: \n341: ```\n342: Scenario: Fake clientset creates AgentRuntime\n343:   GIVEN a fake clientset initialized with Scheme registration\n344:     AND a valid AgentRuntime spec\n345:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is created using the fake client\n346:   THEN the creation succeeds with no error\n347:     AND the AgentRuntime is stored in the fake client's memory\n348:     AND the AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name\n349: \n350: Scenario: Fake clientset updates AgentRuntime\n351:   GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n352:     AND a modified AgentRuntime spec\n353:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is updated using the fake client\n354:   THEN the update succeeds with no error\n355:     AND the AgentRuntime in memory reflects the update\n356:     AND subsequent retrieval returns the updated AgentRuntime\n357: \n358: Scenario: Fake clientset deletes AgentRuntime\n359:   GIVEN a fake clientset with an existing AgentRuntime\n360:   WHEN the AgentRuntime is deleted using the fake client\n361:   THEN the deletion succeeds with no error\n362:     AND the AgentRuntime is removed from memory\n363:     AND subsequent retrieval returns \"not found\" error\n364: \n365: Scenario: Fake clientset watch for AgentRuntimes\n366:   GIVEN a fake clientset\n367:     AND an active watch channel for AgentRuntimes\n368:   WHEN an AgentRuntime is created\n369:   THEN the watch channel receives an ADDED event\n370:     AND the event contains the newly created AgentRuntime\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Test Infrastructure\n376: \n377: ### Test Setup\n378: - Use `test/e2e` package\n379: - Require a running Kubernetes API server (can use envtest for local testing)\n380: - Create temporary test namespaces for isolation\n381: - Clean up test resources after each test\n382: \n383: ### Dependencies\n384: - `k8s.io/client-go` for Kubernetes client\n385: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` for generated clients\n386: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest` for local test environment\n387: \n388: ### Test Naming Convention\n389: - Test functions: `Test<ModuleName>_<ScenarioName>`\n390: - Subtests: `/<GIVEN/WHEN/THEN_Concise_Description>`\n391: \n392: ### Assertions\n393: - Use `assert` package from `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n394: - Verify no errors returned\n395: - Verify returned objects match expected values\n396: - Verify resourceVersion changes on updates\n397: - Verify UID and timestamps on creation\n\n(End of file - total 397 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-041 Delta Specification: E2E 集成测试\n\n## Purpose\nProvide end-to-end integration tests for the agentcube project, covering the complete lifecycle of AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources through the client-go library, including CRUD operations, watch/informer/lister functionality, error handling, and fake client behavior.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: AgentRuntime Lifecycle Integration Tests\n\n**Description**: Verify that AgentRuntime resources can be created, retrieved, updated, status-updated, deleted, and listed through the Kubernetes API server using the client-go library.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- AgentRuntime creation succeeds with valid spec\n- AgentRuntime can be retrieved by name and namespace\n- AgentRuntime spec updates are persisted\n- AgentRuntime status updates are persisted independently of spec\n- AgentRuntime deletion removes the resource\n- AgentRuntime list operations return correct resources\n- Watch operations receive events for AgentRuntime changes\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775897279248,"end":1775897279309}}}}
