ep guide for running tests\n- CI/CD workflow (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`) - existing workflow for running E2E tests in CI\n\n**Total Implementation:** ~3,160 lines of Go test code plus supporting documentation\n\n## Deferred\n\n**Phase 2 & 3 Test Organization**\n- Individual test files (`creation_test.go`, `invocation_test.go`, `execution_test.go`, etc.) - tests consolidated in suite files instead\n\n**Phase 4 Advanced Integration Tests**\n- Dedicated routing integration tests\n- Session management across restarts tests\n- Advanced scalability tests (100 concurrent sessions, 1000 invocations/sec, 100 AgentRuntimes)\n\n**Phase 7: Performance & Security** (Entire Phase Deferred)\n- Load testing utilities and tests (`load_test.go`)\n- Stress testing utilities and tests (`stress_test.go`)\n- Security-focused E2E tests (`security_test.go`)\n- Performance baselines documentation (`BENCHMARKS.md`)\n\n**Phase 6 Documentation**\n- Test patterns documentation (`PATTERNS.md`)\n- Performance baselines (`BENCHMARKS.md`)\n\n**Phase 5 Infrastructure**\n- Custom test reporting with HTML/JSON/JUnit formats (`reporting.go`)","time":{"start":1775897338091,"end":1775897338091}}}
